resenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aChinese literaturevTranslations into English. 0aEnglish literaturevTranslations from Chinese. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh1 aAnrem, Pan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnren, Pan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuilian, Xie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJichang, Ma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnechtges, David R.1 aMaoxian, Zhang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMengjian, Ban, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMingyuan, Bao, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPingzi, Zhahg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPingzi, Zhang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShiheng, Lu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShuye, Xi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWentong, Jiang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWuzhong, Fu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aXiti, Xie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYannian, Yan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYi, Jia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYu, Song, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZ